Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel).

Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two #baking trays{} if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, drain and rinse the @black beans{1%carton} in a #sieve{}. Pop half of
them into a medium #bowl{} and roughly mash with the back of a #fork{}.

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{120%grams}.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Drain the @sweetcorn{160%grams} in a sieve. Heat a large #frying pan{} on high
heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the sweetcorn and cook until charred, ~{5-6%minutes}. Adjust the
heat if necessary. Stir only twice during this time - you want the sweetcorn
to pick up some nice colour.

Transfer the charred corn to a medium bowl, then add the @coleslaw mix{120%grams}
and @mayonnaise{64%grams}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, toss to coat, then
set aside.

Return the (now empty) frying pan to medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once hot, add the garlic and cook, ~{30%seconds}.

Add the black beans (both whole and mashed), @tomato passata{1%carton},
@chipotle paste{20%grams}, @vegetable stock paste{10%grams} and
@sugar{1%tsp}. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Stir to combine and bring to the boil. Simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Lay the @plain taco tortillas{6} on a #board{} (2 per person), spoon the bean
filling down the centre of each, then roll them up to enclose the filling.

Drizzle a little @oil{} over the bottom of an #ovenproof dish{}, then lay in
the wraps. Pack them snugly, side by side, with the folded edge underneath so
they don't unroll. Top with the cheese.

Bake on the middle shelf of your oven until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}.

When the wedges have 5 mins left, remove the tray from the oven. Drizzle with
the @honey{1%tbsp}. Toss to coat, then roast for the remaining time.

When everything's ready, share the enchiladas between your plates. Top with
a dollop of @smashed avocado pot{1}.

Serve the charred corn slaw and wedges alongside. Enjoy!